- VSCode Version: 1.11.1
- OS Version: Windows 10
It was mentioned that this issue was solved before, but I still have it (again).
I work mainly with .ts/TypeScript and .js/JavaScript files, where this problem occurs.

I can work 10 Minutes, up to two hours until Intellisense just freezes, If i press CTRL+Space, it only says "Loading...", but never actually loads the typings up anymore. Hovering over classes or variables doesn't work either anymore, basically nothing at all.
I need to Restart VSCode to have it working again.

I have tried it on a completely fresh install of VSCode, with only TSLint (and also without)
Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create (or clone a existing) Typescript project
2. Work on it until IntelliSense stops working

As mentioned in #19840 I made a new issue because of this.

It is worth noting that we have a good count of files in our Project (200+), but the file sizes themselves are varying. Some are large, and some contain only a single class with a few functions. 

The freezes happen pretty much in any file of any size, but most recently, it happened in a class like this (Was the only content of a file)

```
export interface IRouteConstructor<T> {
    new (widgetParams: T, breadCrumbs: ANYROUTE[]): IRoute<T>
}

export class HierarchyConstructor {
    private readonly routes = new Array<IRoute<{}>>();

    public createAddRoute<T>(ctor: IRouteConstructor<T>, widgetParams: T) {
        const newRoute = new ctor(widgetParams, this.routes.slice());
        this.addRoute(newRoute);
    }
    public addRoute(route: IRoute<{}>) {
        this.routes.push(route);
    }
    public getRoutes() {
        return this.routes;
    }
}
```
